  "title": "Facility Maintenance (Mechanical)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Facility Maintenance (Mechanical)</strong></h3><p><strong>📍 Location:</strong> Tuas (Free shuttle from Choa Chu Kang & Joo Koon MRT)<br /><strong>💰 Attractive Remuneration Package:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Gross Monthly Salary:</strong> Up to <strong>$4,800++</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Base Salary:</strong> Up to $3,800 (for a 4-day work week structure)</p></li><li><p><strong>Additional Allowances:</strong> Shift & transport (typically >$300/month)</p></li><li><p><strong>Overtime Pay & 13th Month Salary</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Performance Bonus:</strong> 1-2 months</p></li><li><p><strong>Schedule Flexibility:</strong> Choose a 5-day or 6-day work week</p></li><li><p><strong>Shift Pattern:</strong> 12-hour rotating shifts (with attractive allowances)</p></li></ul><p><strong>Your Core Mission:</strong></p><p>You will be the go-to expert for all mechanical systems within our plant and facilities, ensuring reliability and driving continuous improvement.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain, troubleshoot, and upgrade plant & facility mechanical equipment.</p></li><li><p>Quickly diagnose and resolve equipment issues to minimize production downtime.</p></li><li><p>Conduct routine inspections, testing, and checks using industry best practices.</p></li><li><p>Uphold the highest standards of safety and housekeeping at all times.</p></li><li><p>Actively support Preventive Maintenance and Continuous Improvement projects.</p></li><li><p>Help drive high production line efficiency and performance.</p></li><li><p>Guide and train junior technicians and operators as needed.</p></li></ul><p><strong>We’re Looking For Someone With:</strong></p><ul><li><p>A <strong>NITEC / Higher NITEC / Diploma in Mechanical Engineering</strong> or equivalent.</p></li><li><p><strong>Proven hands-on experience</strong> with facility systems like <strong>Chillers, Air Handling Units (AHUs), compressors, and boilers</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Practical skills in <strong>metal fabrication and using mechanical tools</strong> (e.g., welding, drilling).</p></li><li><p>The ability to <strong>read and interpret mechanical drawings and specifications</strong>.</p></li><li><p>A strong knack for <strong>troubleshooting complex mechanical systems</strong>.</p></li><li><p>A willingness to <strong>guide others</strong> and share knowledge.</p></li><li><p>Flexibility to work <strong>rotating shifts and overtime</strong> when required.<br /></p><p></p></li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p>EA Personnel R22110043 Tan Eng Kang</p><p>EA License 21C0430 A Dreamworks Company Pte Ltd</p>",
